# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (changes to documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding tests, refactoring test; no production code change)
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   build    (build system or external dependencies)
#   ci       (continuous integration)
#   revert   (reverts a previous commit)
#
# Scope is optional and can be anything specifying place of the commit change.
# For example: frontend, backend, database, docker, docs, etc.
#
# Subject should be under 50 characters and describe what changed
# Body should explain what and why vs. how (optional)
# Footer should contain any BREAKING CHANGE or issue references (optional)
#
# Examples:
# feat(auth): add OAuth2 integration for user authentication
# fix(database): resolve connection timeout in MySQL queries
# docs(readme): update installation instructions for Docker setup
# style(frontend): format React components with prettier
# refactor(api): extract common validation logic into utility functions